- Reintroduces the `Stream` trait to clean up the connections API.
- Adds an `OperatorStream` type which is returned when connecting operators.
- Adds a `PyStream` base class which functions similarly to the Rust `Stream` trait.
- Updates the rust toolchain due to a compiler bug present in the previous nightly.

The advantage of this PR is that it clarifies the Rust API when connecting operators, and uses type checking to prevent certain erroneous patterns that were previously possible, e.g. connecting an IngestStream to a loop by doing the following:
```rust
let ingest_stream = IngestStream::new();
let loop_stream = LoopStream::new();
loop_stream.connect_loop(&Stream::from(&ingest_stream));
```
